BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-trip-005@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260915
SUMMARY:[Book] TRA Fangliao to Taitung to Ruisui (Sep 29)
DESCRIPTION:TRA tickets available today for Sep 29.\nRoute: Fangliao to Tai
 tung (South-Link) to Ruisui (northbound).\nNew EMU3000 trains - no standin
 g tickets!\nMost beautiful coastal railway in Taiwan.\nApp: Taiwan Railway
  e-Booking or railway.gov.tw.\nNeed: passport number.
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-trip-006@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260916
SUMMARY:[Book] TRA Ruisui to Taitung to Kaohsiung (Sep 30)
DESCRIPTION:TRA tickets available today for Sep 30.\nRoute: Ruisui to Taitu
 ng (southbound) to Kaohsiung (South-Link).\nApp: Taiwan Railway e-Booking 
 or railway.gov.tw.\nNeed: passport number.
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-trip-007@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260917
SUMMARY:[Check] TRA backup plan for Sep 30
DESCRIPTION:If Sep 16 booking failed, can buy separately:\nSep 30 Ruisui to
  Taitung + Taitung to Kaohsiung (South-Link).\nTaitung to Kaohsiung also n
 eeds 14-day advance booking.
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-trip-008@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260918
SUMMARY:[Flight] Depart Zwijndrecht to Taipei via Amsterdam 11:00
DESCRIPTION:Departure day schedule:\n04:30 Wake up\n05:00 Final luggage che
 ck (passport / Entry Permit / tickets / EUR 300-500 cash / debit card / tr
 avel insurance)\n05:30 Train from Zwijndrecht to Rotterdam Centraal to Sch
 iphol Airport (~1.5-2h with transfer)\n07:30 Arrive at Schiphol Airport\n0
 7:30-08:30 Check-in / baggage drop / security\n09:00 Through security, hea
 d to gate\n11:00 Flight departs Amsterdam to Taipei\n\nTrain route: Zwijnd
 recht -> Rotterdam Centraal -> Schiphol.\nSleep early the night before! Ch
 eck NS App for first train schedule (~05:00).
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-trip-009@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260923
SUMMARY:[Buy] Alishan Sunrise Train Ticket (Sep 24 early morning)
DESCRIPTION:Must buy today afternoon!\nTime: 1:00 PM - 4:00 PM (sales open 
 at 1 PM, sells out fast!)\nLocation: Alishan Station\nArrive before 12:30 
 to queue!\nThis is the Zhushan Line train ticket for tomorrow sunrise view
 ing.
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-trip-010@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260919
SUMMARY:[Arrive] Taipei 06:15
DESCRIPTION:Arrive Taoyuan Airport (TPE) at 06:15.\n\nToday's plan:\n1. Air
 port MRT to city\n2. Drop bags at hotel\n3. Buy EasyCard + SIM card + exch
 ange TWD\n4. Rest to adjust to jet lag\n5. 3-4 PM: Elephant Mountain for T
 aipei 101 photo\n6. Evening: Ningxia Night Market
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-trip-011@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261004
SUMMARY:[Flight] Depart Kaohsiung to Nanjing 11:40
DESCRIPTION:Flight: Kaohsiung (KHH) to Nanjing.\nDepart: 11:40. Arrive: 14:
 00.\n\nReminders:\n- Kaohsiung Airport customs is fast, arrive 2-2.5 hours
  before\n- 09:00-09:30 leave hotel\n- This is Day 15 of Entry Permit (last
  legal day)! Must depart today!
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-trip-012@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261005
SUMMARY:[Flight] Nanjing to Taiyuan 07:40
DESCRIPTION:Flight: Nanjing to Taiyuan.\nDepart: 07:40. Arrive: 09:40.\n\nA
 rrive at airport by 05:40.\nTrip complete! Home!
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-food-001@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260912
SUMMARY:[Food] Book A-Hsia Restaurant Tainan (Sep 26 dinner)
DESCRIPTION:Michelin-recommended Taiwanese cuisine, very popular!\nDinner d
 ate: Sep 26.\nBooking: Download inline APP, book 1-2 weeks ahead.\nBook no
 w - popular time slots fill up!\nAddress: Tainan, West Central Dist, Zhong
 yi Rd Sec 2 Lane 84 No 16.
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-food-002@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261002
SUMMARY:[Food] Book Re-chao Restaurant Kaohsiung (Oct 3 dinner)
DESCRIPTION:Last night Taiwanese stir-fry dinner! With Taiwan Beer.\nDinner
  date: Oct 3.\nRecommended: Hai-Bao Seafood / Sha-Ka-Dang.\nBooking: Call 
 1 day ahead (weekends get busy).\nCall today after arriving in Kaohsiung t
 o book tomorrow night!
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-food-003@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260919
SUMMARY:[Arrive] Buy EasyCard + SIM card + Exchange TWD at airport
DESCRIPTION:First things to do after arriving at Taoyuan Airport:\n1. Excha
 nge TWD: Terminal 2 Floor 1 Bank of Taiwan / Mega Bank (bring EUR 300-500)
 \n2. Chunghwa Telecom SIM card: need passport, ~10 min, NT$300-500 unlimit
 ed data\n3. Buy EasyCard: airport convenience store (deposit NT$100) + top
  up NT$1000\n\nAll three can be done inside the airport terminal!
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-food-004@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260920
SUMMARY:[Food] Fu Hang Soy Milk - arrive before 7:30 AM!
DESCRIPTION:Taipei's most famous breakfast spot!\nArrive before 7:30 AM to 
 avoid 30-60 min queue.\nLocation: Near Shandao Temple Station, Zhongxiao E
  Rd Sec 1 No 108.\nMust order: thick flatbread with egg, salty soy milk.\n
 Queue is serious even on weekdays!
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-food-005@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260926
SUMMARY:[Food] Tainan queue restaurants today!
DESCRIPTION:Tainan food day - two famous queue spots:\n\n1. A-Tang Savory P
 orridge: opens 06:00, queue 1hr+. Go early!\n   Address: Tainan, West Cent
 ral Dist, Ximen Rd Sec 1 No 728.\n\n2. Liu-Qian Beef Soup (optional): open
 s 05:00! Limited quantity.\n   Address: Tainan, West Central Dist, Haian R
 d Sec 1 No 63.\n\nA-Hsia Restaurant tonight (already booked via inline APP
 ).
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-food-006@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260924
SUMMARY:[Food] Alishan sunrise ticket + confirm rafting booking
DESCRIPTION:Today at Alishan:\nGo to Alishan Station before 1 PM to queue f
 or tomorrow's sunrise train ticket! (Already in transport reminders)\n\nAl
 so confirm: Xiuguluan River Rafting (Sep 30) is booked on Klook/KKday?\nIf
  not booked yet, book today!
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-food-007@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260925
SUMMARY:[Food] Chiayi Turkey Rice for lunch!
DESCRIPTION:On the way down from Alishan to Tainan, must stop in Chiayi for
  turkey rice!\n\nRecommended: any local shop near Chiayi Station.\nOr Lin-
 Cong-Ming sand-pot fish head nearby.\n\nThis is the first hot meal after d
 escending - super satisfying!
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260625T000000Z
UID:tw-food-008@taiwan-itinerary
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260928
SUMMARY:[Food] Houpihu Seafood for lunch in Kenting!
DESCRIPTION:Today in Kenting, lunch at Houpihu seafood!\n\nRecommended: A-X
 ing Sashimi.\nBest value seafood in Taiwan! Sashimi from NT$100.\nMonday =
  fewer people, shorter queue.\nAddress: Pingtung, Hengchun, Daguang Rd No 
 79-30.
END:VEVENT

END:VCALENDAR

